This isn't necessarily true - without knowledge of how the data may be encrypted and what processes are involved in decrypting the data, one can't make the "it isn't secure" statement.

That being said, it is probably safe to argue that sites that do not require PCI, SOX, HIPPA, etc would be less inclined to engage in this level of security.  But that doesn't mean that it is not being done.

t

